item.title: Applications: Datasets formats
item.description:
As a customer, you can access Insights data via BigQuery Dataset or as Exported Table Data to Cloud Storage BigQuery BigQuery is a “big data” SQL store invented by Google. Many massive datasets, like all the code in GitHub and the complete history of the Bitcoin blockchain, are made available to the public through the Google BigQuery Datasets initiative. BigQuery Datasets are multi-terabyte datasets hosted on Google’s servers. You interact with the dataset by writing SQL fetch queries within either the web UI, Command-line tool or any client library.
